      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Berberine gained the nickname "Nature\'s Ozempic" on social media platforms like TikTok because both compounds influence metabolic pathways related to blood sugar and weight management. However, they work through completely different mechanisms. Ozempic is a GLP-1 receptor agonist, while berberine activates AMPK, an enzyme involved in cellular energy regulation. The comparison is largely marketing-driven rather than scientifically precise.' },
